councillor stephane (env) would like to express dissapointment with the
confusion that is being created with teh new watcard/bus pass. there is a lot
of telephone talk as people try to figure out what is going on. 

the vped responded that the upass is split between vpe and vpof. GRT hasn't 
decided exactly how the process is going to move ahead. it's confusing for
feds because data is shared between teh university (watcard office) and GRT, 
whereas the agreement is between GRT and Feds. Students will have an interim
period where the card will be excepted without tap, and students will still
have the leeway term (pay for two terms, the card works in teh third if you
are off-campus).

The councillor re-iterated that there should be mroe comunication and that
while recognizing ti isn't in feds control, the vpe should push GRT to be
more transparent.

communication with students saying that that they need to replace their 
watcard, email blast went out. 

it was made clear that students will always have access to paying teh upass 
fee as opposed to teh GRT standard fare.

Andrew will go to negotiations with teh feedback and will try to get more info 
up on watcard site and feds, and will email councillors with more information

